博碩士論文 etd-0708115-110348 詳細資訊




首頁 > 網路資源 > 大同大學數位論文系統
博碩士論文 etd-0708115-110348 詳細資訊











下載電子全文宣告
										本論文權限為 校內一年後公開，校外永不公開
故現在無法讓您下載 
您的連線位址是 104.199.203.235
論文繳交時間是 2015-07-08
現在時間是 2017-07-21
論文開放時間是 校外不公開






姓名
何惠淳 (Hui-Chun Ho)
電子郵件信箱
不公開


系所
生物工程學系(所) (Bioengineering)


學位
碩士 (Master)
學年 / 學期
103 學年第 2 學期

論文名稱(中)
應用計畫行為理論探討女性遵守坐月子習俗之行為意圖與實際行為

論文名稱(英)
Application of the Theory of Planned Behavior to Postpartum Care (Tso-Yueh-Tzu) Intention and Behavior among Married Mothers

檔案

etd-0708115-110348.pdf

本電子全文僅授權使用者為學術研究之目的，進行個人非營利性質之檢索、閱讀、列印。
        			 請遵守中華民國著作權法之相關規定，切勿任意重製、散佈、改作、轉貼、播送，以免觸法。

論文使用權限
校內一年後公開，校外永不公開

論文種類
碩士論文


論文語文別 / 頁數
中文 / 99

統計
已被瀏覽 593 次，被下載 1 次

關鍵字(中)
坐月子
計畫行為理論
行為意圖

關鍵字(英)
the theory of planned behavior
behavioral intention
postpartum care


摘要(中)
摘要  本研究採問捲調查法，以「計畫行為理論」為架構，分析影響女性遵守坐月子習俗的行為意圖之因素。研究對象為桃園市已婚且具生育經驗的女性，有效問捲共計150份，所得資料以描述性統計法、t檢定、單因子變異數分析、皮爾森積差相關及多元迴歸分析等統計方法進行討論，所得的研究結果如下：一、女性遵守坐月子習俗行為意圖的現況呈正向狀態。二、不同背景變項的女性在遵守坐月子習俗各層面之差異情形。（一）不同「主要照顧者」的女性在遵守坐月子習俗之各層面有顯著差異。（二）不同「年齡」、「生產型式」、「家庭型態」及「坐月子地點」的女性在遵守坐   月子習俗之各層面有部分差異。（三）不同「教育程度」的女性在遵守坐月子習俗之各層面無顯著差異。三、女性遵守坐月子習俗的「態度」、「主觀規範」、「知覺行為控制」及「行為意圖」  間具顯著相關。四、女性遵守坐月子習俗的「態度」、「主觀規範」、「知覺行為控制」對「行為意圖」  的聯合預測變異量達36.1%。其中以「態度」最具預測力，「知覺行為控制」次  之，「主觀規範」最低。五、「知覺行為控制」與「行為意圖」對女性遵守坐月子習俗「實際行為」（飲食規  範與禁忌）的聯合預測變異量達40.5%，對女性遵守坐月子習俗「實際行為」（行  為禁忌）的聯合預測變異量亦達33.1%。而「行為意圖」皆較「知覺行為控制」  更具預測力。  最後，依據研究結果加以討論，並提出具體建議，以提供護理人員、準媽媽們及未來研究者作為參考。關鍵詞：行為意圖、計畫行為理論、坐月子

摘要(英)
ABSTRACT   From the perspective of Theory of Planned Behavior (TPB), the research analyzed the factors influencing married mothers’ behavioral intention of postpartum care (Tso-Yueh-Tzu). The participants were married mothers in Taoyuan City. In all, 150 valid questionnaires were retrieved. Descriptive analysis, t-test, one-way ANOVA, Pearson product-moment correlation, step-wise multiple regression analysis were used for data analysis. The results are as follows:1. The level of current married mothers’ behavioral intention of postpartum care was high.2. The differences in postpartum care among married mothers from different backgrounds  are as follows:(1) There was significant difference in all aspects of postpartum care among married   mothers under postnatal care of different caregivers.(2) There were significant differences in some aspects of postpartum care among married   mothers of different ages, delivery modes, family structures, and postpartum care  places.(3) There was no significant difference in all aspects of postpartum care among married   mothers of different educational backgrounds.3. Statistically significant positive correlations were found among “attitude”, “subjective  norm”, “perceived behavioral control”, and “behavioral intention” of married mothers’  postpartum care.4. The TPB model was found significant by regression analysis, which interprets the variance of 36.1% of behavioral intention. Attitude, subjective norm, and perceived  behavioral control could positively predict behavioral intention. Attitude was the strongest predictor among the three while perceived behavioral control was better  than subjective norm.5. Married mothers’ perceived behavioral control and behavioral intention accounted for  40.5 % and 33.1% of the predicted variance in their practice of the postpartum dietary  guidelines and their obedience to the postpartum behavior taboos, respectively. Of the  two, behavioral intention was the stronger predictor.  Finally, suggestions based on the research results were proposed for the reference of nursing staffs, expectant mothers and researchers.Keywords:behavioral intention, the theory of planned behavior, postpartum care .

論文目次
